# Admin Web — KYC Status on Hosts & Clients Lists

This document describes how the **admin web repo** should display a KYC verification
badge (`Not Started`, `Verified`, `Failed`, `Pending`) on every row of the existing
**Hosts** and **Clients** list screens.

It documents what the backend (`opabackend`) currently exposes, the canonical status
mapping, and the recommended integration path.

---

## 1. KYC status values

The backend stores KYC results in the `host_kycs` and `client_kycs` tables. The
`status` column is written by the Dojah webhook (`app/services/dojah_kyc.py`) and only
ever holds one of three values. A fourth value, `not_started`, is **derived** (it means
"no KYC row exists for this user").

| Backend value  | When it happens                                                                 | UI label      | Suggested colour |
|----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------|------------------|
| `not_started`  | User has no KYC record at all (never launched the Dojah widget).                | **Not Started** | grey / neutral |
| `pending`      | KYC row created, awaiting Dojah decision (widget launched, webhook not final).  | **Pending**     | amber / yellow |
| `approved`     | Dojah returned `Completed` / `verified` / `success`.                            | **Verified**    | green |
| `declined`     | Dojah returned `failed` / `rejected` / `error` / `declined`.                    | **Failed**      | red |

> **Mapping is fixed** — the admin web should map exactly:
> `not_started → Not Started`, `pending → Pending`, `approved → Verified`, `declined → Failed`.
> Treat any unexpected value as `Not Started`.

### Note on "stale pending"
The end-user (host/client app) status endpoints downgrade a `pending` row older than
30 minutes back to `not_started` so the user can restart. **The admin endpoints do NOT
do this** — admins see the true DB status (`pending` stays `pending`). This is
intentional so admins can see abandoned/in-progress attempts.

