## 2. Authentication

All endpoints below require an **admin** JWT:

```
Authorization: Bearer <admin_access_token>
```

Base URL prefix for every route: `/api/v1`.

---

## 3. Existing backend endpoints (available today)

In addition to the `kyc_status` field now returned on the main list endpoints (Option A,
see §4–§5), the backend offers four dedicated, paginated, admin-only endpoints that filter
by KYC outcome.

### 3.1 Hosts who completed KYC (`approved` only)

```
GET /api/v1/hosts/kyc/completed?page=1&limit=50
```

Response:

```jsonc
{
  "total": 12,
  "page": 1,
  "limit": 50,
  "total_pages": 1,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 42,
      "full_name": "Jane Doe",
      "email": "jane@example.com",
      "mobile_number": "+2547...",
      "kyc_verified_name": "JANE DOE",
      "kyc_verified_dob": "1990-04-12",
      "kyc_verified_at": "2026-05-30T10:15:00Z",
      "kyc_document_type": "ke-id",
      "kyc_face_match_score": 0.98
    }
  ]
}
```

Every row here is implicitly **Verified**.

### 3.2 Hosts who have NOT completed KYC (`pending`, `declined`, or no record)

```
GET /api/v1/hosts/kyc/incomplete?page=1&limit=50
```

Response:

```jsonc
{
  "total": 130,
  "page": 1,
  "limit": 50,
  "total_pages": 3,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 77,
      "full_name": "John Smith",
      "email": "john@example.com",
      "mobile_number": "+2547...",
      "kyc_status": "pending",          // "pending" | "declined" | "not_started"
      "kyc_verified_name": null,
      "kyc_verified_dob": null,
      "kyc_created_at": "2026-06-01T08:00:00Z",
      "kyc_document_type": null,
      "kyc_decision_reason": null        // populated with the failure message when declined
    }
  ]
}
```

Each row carries its own `kyc_status` → map to **Pending** / **Failed** / **Not Started**.

### 3.3 Clients — identical shape

```
GET /api/v1/clients/kyc/completed?page=1&limit=50
GET /api/v1/clients/kyc/incomplete?page=1&limit=50
```

Same response structure as the host endpoints (rows use `id, full_name, email,
mobile_number, kyc_*`).

### Query params (all four)
- `page` — integer, `>= 1`, default `1`.
- `limit` — integer, `1..100`, default `50`.

