## 5. Backend implementation (Option A — done)

Files: `app/schemas.py` and `app/admin/users.py`.

1. `kyc_status: str = "not_started"` added to `HostListResponse` and `ClientListResponse`.
2. A shared `_kyc_status_map(db, kyc_model, owner_col, owner_ids)` helper resolves the
   status for the page's users in **two queries**: one for `approved` (always wins) and
   one ordered newest-first for everyone else (first row seen per user = latest attempt).
   `list_hosts` / `list_clients` call it for the current page only and default missing
   users to `not_started`.

Precedence per user: `approved` wins regardless of recency; otherwise the most recent row
by `created_at`. This keeps search, sort, and pagination intact and adds **no** per-row
round-trips (two extra queries per page, mirroring the existing `cars_counts`/`pm_counts`
batch pattern).

---

## 6. Summary

- KYC has exactly 4 states for the UI: **Not Started / Pending / Verified / Failed**,
  mapped from backend `not_started / pending / approved / declined`.
- `/api/v1/admin/hosts` and `/api/v1/admin/clients` now return `kyc_status` per row
  (Option A) — render one badge column, no extra requests.
- Four filter endpoints (`{hosts,clients}/kyc/{completed,incomplete}`) remain available
  for KYC-only screens; Option B (client-side merge) is the fallback.
